name: Nike SB Dunk Low Raygun Tie-Dye White
description: The Dunk SB Low 'Tie-Dye Raygun - White' released exclusively at select skate shops in January 2020. Bringing back a design from the Pink Box era, the shoe's upper features tie-dye patterns to pay tribute to the late Sandy Bodecker, who helped luanch Nike's skateboarding division. The lateral heel includes a graphic drawing from the Roswell Rayguns of Nike's 2002 ad campaign, while Zoom Air in the sockliner provides cushioning.
